This paper deals with image representation and deep neural networks, which are primarily studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories of arXiv CS. The paper also involves developing a non-linear mapping, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the experiments involve benchmark image datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper's focus on dimensionality reduction and optimization aligns with the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
